headline: BD and Ypsomed’s Large‑Volume Biologic Autoinjector Collaboration Could Be A Game Changer For Becton Dickinson (BDX)
summary: BD (Becton, Dickinson and Company) and Ypsomed recently expanded their collaboration to develop a 5.5 mL BD Neopak XtraFlow Glass Prefillable Syringe compatible with Ypsomed's YpsoMate 5.5 autoinjector, targeting large-volume, high-viscosity biologic self-injections. This move highlights BD's push deeper into large-volume subcutaneous drug delivery, aiming to make complex biologic treatments more practical for at-home use. Next, we’ll examine how BD’s expanded large-volume biologics platform...

headline: BD and Ypsomed Expand Partnership to Target Growing Biologics Market
summary: BDX expands its Ypsomed partnership with a 5.5 mL Neopak XtraFlow syringe, targeting rising demand for large-volume subcutaneous self-injection.

headline: BD and Ypsomed develop new version of Neopak XtraFlow syringe
summary: The new 5.5ml BD Neopak XtraFlow Syringe uses BD’s advanced technologies, including thinner cannulas.
